    "name": "Gli Alunni Del Sole",
    "profile": "Italian pop band born in Naples at end of 1960s as [b]I Maronti[/b] by brothers [a=Bruno Morelli (2)] (guitar) and [a=Paolo Morelli] (piano and vocals), who moved to Rome meeting [a=Giulio Leofrigio] (drums) and [a=Giampaolo Borra] (bass). First singles released with [l=Parade] were a resounding hits: \"[i]L'Aquilone[/i]\" (1968) and \"[i]Concerto[/i]\" (1969) where we already find traces of prog rock, but later prevails the Neapolitan lyricism of singer-songwriter Paolo Morelli. It's enough to listen his best romantic hit \"[i]A Canzuncella[/i]\" (1977). \r\n\r\n● [a=Paolo Morelli] – vocals, piano (1968-2013)\r\n● [a=Bruno Morelli (2)] – vocals, guitar (1968-)\r\n● [a=Giulio Leofrigio] – drums (1968-1979)\r\n● [a=Giampaolo Borra] – bass (1968-1979)\r\n● Antonio Rapicavoli – sax (1968-1970)\r\n● [a=Ruggero Stefani] – drums (1979-)\r\n● [a=Gianfranco Coletta] – bass, guitar (1979-)\r\n● Alessandro Saba – bass (1996-)\r\n● [a=Enrico Olivieri] – keyboards (1996-)",
